                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Moose, James S./417: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shullaw</hi>
                    </persName>
                    <note n="5" xml:id="d865fn5">Mr. Moose was at this time in the United States on
                        consultation and leave.</note>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-14T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 14, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. The President desires to appoint Mr. James S. Moose, Jr. to act as Minister
                    Resident to Saudi Arabia.</p>
                <p>Please ascertain whether Mr. Moose’s appointment would be agreeable to the
                    Government of Saudi Arabia and telegraph reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
